<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Left handed mouse in Excel]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=249&amp;p=1102#p1102"><![CDATA[
Classic Shell doesn't do anything to change mouse behavior inside other applications. That is unrelated. Check in All Programs -&gt; Start Menu Settings -&gt; Controls tab (All Settings) or &quot;Basic Settings&quot; tab to see if &quot;Left Click Opens&quot; is set to &quot;Classic Start Menu&quot;,  not &quot;Windows Start Menu&quot;. The left column in your Windows Start Menu might be empty because the Most Frequently Used program history is off. Turn it on by right clicking the taskbar -&gt; Properties -&gt; Start Menu tab -&gt; Check &quot;Store recently opened programs&quot;.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue Feb 12, 2013 7:44 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
